2026-05-22 22:31:11,732 | INFO | [iter=0] REVIEW rejected  confidence=95  missing=[]  reason=All required entities and semantic_resolved_filters (location_name Baner, property_type Flat, transaction_category Sale, year 2024) are present and correctly applied, satisfying entity completeness. However, the analysis_type is rate_trend, which per the instructions must compute a rate metric using both agreement_price and net_carpet_area_sq_m (with the standard rate_per_sq_ft formula). The provided SQL only counts agreement_price and does not calculate any rate or use net_carpet_area_sq_m, so it does not satisfy the Stage 2 rate_trend algorithm requirements. The suggested fix introduces a proper rate_per_sq_ft metric using SUM(agreement_price)/SUM(net_carpet_area_sq_m)/10.764 with NULLIF protection, preserves the transaction count as requested by the metric description, and keeps the same time-based grouping and ordering for the trend.
2026-05-22 22:31:11,733 | INFO | [iter=0] REVIEW — applying reviewer's corrected SQL
2026-05-22 22:31:11,733 | INFO | [iter=0] EXECUTE — SELECT
  year,
  quarter,
  location_name,
  location_latitude,
  location_longitude,
  ROUND(
    SUM(agreement_price) / NULLIF(SUM(net_carpet_area_sq_m), 0) / 10.764,
    2
  ) AS rate_per_sq_ft,
  COUNT(agreement_price) AS "residential sale transactions"
FROM transactions
WHERE
  (location_name ILIKE '%Baner%' OR sub_locality ILIKE '%Baner%' OR micro_market ILIKE '%Baner%')
  AND property_type IN ('Flat')
  AND transaction_category IN ('Sale')
  AND year = 2024
  AND agreement_price >= 1
  AND net_carpet_area_sq_m IS NOT NULL
GROUP BY
  year,
  quarter,
  location_name,
  location_latitude,
  location_longitude
ORDER BY
  year ASC,
  quarter ASC;
